{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/iostreamprotocol\/close(cancellable:)-v737"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStreamProtocol"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it. This will also"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"close the individual input and output streams, if they are not already","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"closed."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"CancellableT"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CancellableT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CancellableT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol","text":"CancellableProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO19CancellableProtocolP","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once the stream is closed, all other operations will return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closed"},{"type":"text","text":". Closing a stream multiple times will not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"return an error."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Closing a stream will automatically flush any outstanding buffers"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the stream."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Streams will be automatically closed when the last reference","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is dropped, but you might want to call this function to make sure"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"resources are released as early as possible.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some streams might keep the backing store of the stream (e.g. a file","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"descriptor) open after the stream is closed. See the documentation for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the individual stream for details.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On failure the first error that happened will be reported, but the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"close operation will finish as much as possible. A stream that failed"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to close will still return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closed"},{"type":"text","text":" for all operations."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Still, it is important to check and report the error to the user,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"otherwise there might be a loss of data as all data might not be written.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not NULL, then the operation can be cancelled by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"was cancelled, the error ","type":"text"},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Cancelling a close will still leave the stream closed, but some streams"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can use a faster close that doesn’t block to e.g. check errors.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of this method just calls close on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"individual input\/output streams.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStreamProtocol\/close(cancellable:)-v737"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"close"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"CancellableT"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableT"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO16IOStreamProtocolPAAE5close11cancellableSbqd__Sg_tKAA011CancellableC0Rd__lF","title":"close(cancellable:)","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GIO"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/IOStreamProtocol":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IOStreamProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"IOStreamProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStreamProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/iostreamprotocol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOStream"},{"text":" represents an object that has both read and write streams.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Generally the two streams act as separate input and output streams,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but they share some common resources and state. For instance, for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"seekable streams, both streams may use the same position."}],"title":"IOStreamProtocol","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/IOStreamProtocol/close(cancellable:)-v737":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStreamProtocol\/close(cancellable:)-v737","title":"close(cancellable:)","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/iostreamprotocol\/close(cancellable:)-v737","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it. This will also"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"close the individual input and output streams, if they are not already","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"closed.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"CancellableT"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CancellableT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableProtocol":{"role":"symbol","title":"CancellableProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CancellableProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GCancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol"}}}